<br>
Fortunately, the subscription price of EverQuest had remained a constant ten dollars a month for a very long time.  The recent price increase was most likely imposed because of very straightforward reasons.  Basically, given the lack of competition including how some of the attempted competitors failed rather miserably, they could have increased prices therefor they *did* increase prices.  Theres no Burger King of the MMORPG world, Taco Bell reigns supreme (or Quizzno's, you pick it :) )<br>
<br>
For those that want to go along with the "crack dealer" analogy, thats fine but VI is a business.  Even more simply put: Welcome to corporate America, your in our world now.<br>
<br>
On a side note, an outside company should do an audited research article to report VI's actual hardware needs.  With such a report available, perhaps the EverQuest community could refute VI's publicly stated reason for the price increase.  Otherwise, there appears to be really no way for the public to know whether VI's statement is fabricated.  I believe their reasons were something along the lines of, "blah blah due to a larger customer base etc etc we have to upgrade stuff blah blah gimme gimme gimme."<br>
<br>
True their customer support is lacking and hopefully will be addressed sometime soon.  On the other hand, take that lack with a grain of salt and take a look at what VI and SOE have created, maintained, and modified with very few hiccups.  The release of Luclin could have been a little smoother, but as a whole the game is remarkable.  At the very least, put in your complaint about the customer support and then move past it.  There are plenty of other resources available that can help EverQuest customers with technical problems.<br>
<br>
I have an Asus A7A266 motherboard, PC2100 RAM, Athlon 1200, a SBLive! Value, Asus V7100, and WinXP.  I have yet to encounter a problem with EverQuest, any kind of problem.  I cant stand playing EverQuest without having MP3's playing in the background.  Make sure you have the newest BIOS and drivers for your motherboard, sound card, and any other devices. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucarathosollathir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carathos Ollathir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1396<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/27/02 2:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3211.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Why doesnt Taco Bell charge five bucks for a bean burrito? They cant because if they did, customers would choose Burger King every time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That's retarded.  You think Taco Bell's prices have remained the same since the day they opened?  Nope.  Also, if there are items that HAVE remained the same, have they improved in any way?  Nope, same old taco.<br>
